Helm Bank Sells 300 Billion Pesos of Securities in Colombia

-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 
2011-08-03T21:13:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/helm-bank-sells-300-billion-pesos-of-securities-in-colombia-1-.html
Helm Bank SA (PFBHELMB) , a Colombian lender,
sold 300 billion pesos ($169 million) of bonds in the domestic
market, the stock exchange said in an e-mailed statement.  The bank, formerly known as Banco de Credito, sold 36-month
securities to yield 1.95 percentage points above the IBR
interbank rate,  Colombia â€™s stock exchange said in an e-mailed
statement. Helm Bank also sold 60- and 84-month debt to yield
4.08 and 4.35 percentage points above inflation, respectively,
according to the statement.  The lender also sold 84-month bonds in inflation-linked
currency units known as UVR to yield 4.58 percent. Investor
demand for the securities totaled 751.5 billion pesos, according
to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
